.TH "add_timer_on" 9 "add_timer_on" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
add_timer_on \- start a timer on a particular CPU
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" add_timer_on
.BI "(struct timer_list *timer "  ","
.BI "int cpu "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "timer" 12
the timer to be added
.IP "cpu" 12
the CPU to start it on
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is not very scalable on SMP. Double adds are not possible.
